'''認知偏誤'''（{{lang-en|Cognitive bias}} <ref>{{Cite web|title=Cognitive Bias, Encyclopedia of Animal Cognition and Behavior,SpringerLink|url=https://link.springer.com/referenceworkentry/10.1007%2F978-3-319-47829-6_1244-1}}</ref>），或作'''認知偏差'''<ref>{{Cite web|title=[H27] 認知偏差|url=http://philosophy.hku.hk/think/chi/bias.php|accessdate=2016-08-07|author=劉彥方 陳強立|date=|last=|first=|authorlink=|coauthors=|year=|month=|format=|work=|publisher=思方網|pages=|language=|doi=|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200202170953/https://philosophy.hku.hk/think/chi/bias.php|archivedate=2020-02-02|dead-url=no|quote=}}</ref>、'''認知偏見'''<ref>{{Cite web|title=cognitive bias - 認知偏見|url=http://terms.naer.edu.tw/detail/2097865/|accessdate=2016-08-07|author=|date=|last=|first=|authorlink=|coauthors=|year=|month=|format=|work=|publisher=國家教育研究院|pages=|language=|doi=|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160817201305/http://terms.naer.edu.tw/detail/2097865/|archivedate=2016-08-17|deadurl=yes|quote=}}</ref>等，是一種在判斷中偏離規範（英語：norm，哲學術語）或理性的系統模式。<ref name="Haselton_2005">{{cite book|vauthors=Haselton MG, Nettle D, Andrews PW|chapter=The evolution of cognitive bias.|year=2005|location=Hoboken, NJ, US|publisher=John Wiley & Sons Inc|veditors=Buss DM|title=The Handbook of Evolutionary Psychology|pages=724–746}}</ref> 個人根據他們對輸入的感知創造他們自己的“主觀現實”。個人對現實的建構，而不是[[客觀性|客觀]]輸入，可能會決定他們在世界上的[[行為|行為]]。因此，認知偏差有時可能會導致知覺扭曲、不准確的判斷、不合邏輯的解釋或廣義上的非理性（英語：irrationality）。<ref>{{cite journal|title=Subjective probability: A judgment of representativeness|url=http://datacolada.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/Kahneman-Tversky-1972.pdf|journal=Cognitive Psychology|issue=3|doi=10.1016/0010-0285(72)90016-3|year=1972|volume=3|pages=430–454|vauthors=Kahneman D, Tversky A|access-date=2017-04-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191214120047/http://datacolada.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/Kahneman-Tversky-1972.pdf|archive-date=2019-12-14|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|vauthors=Baron J|date=2007|title=Thinking and Deciding|edition=4th|location=New York, NY|publisher=Cambridge University Press}}</ref><ref name="Ariely.2008">{{cite book|last=Ariely|first=Dan|name-list-style=vanc|author-link=Dan Ariely|year=2008|title=Predictably Irrational: The Hidden Forces That Shape Our Decisions|location=New York, NY|publisher=[[HarperCollins|HarperCollins]]|isbn=978-0-06-135323-9|title-link=Predictably Irrational}}</ref>

儘管這種誤解看起來像是失常，但偏見可以幫助人類找到共同點和捷徑，以幫助處理生活中的常見情況。<ref>{{Cite web|title=12 Common Biases That Affect How We Make Everyday Decisions|url=https://www.psychologytoday.com/blog/thoughts-thinking/201809/12-common-biases-affect-how-we-make-everyday-decisions|access-date=2020-07-21|website=Psychology Today|language=en-US}}</ref>

一些認知偏差大概是適應性的。認知偏差可能會導致在特定情況下採取更有效的行動。<ref>For instance: {{cite journal|title=Reasoning the fast and frugal way: models of bounded rationality|url=http://library.mpib-berlin.mpg.de/ft/gg/gg_reasoning_1996.pdf|date=October 1996|journal=Psychological Review|issue=4|doi=10.1037/0033-295X.103.4.650|volume=103|pages=650–69|pmid=8888650|vauthors=Gigerenzer G, Goldstein DG|citeseerx=10.1.1.174.4404}}</ref> 此外，允許認知偏差可以實現更快的決策，當及時性比準確性更有價值時，這可能是可取的，如[[啟發法|啟發法]]所示。<ref name="h_and_b">{{cite journal|title=Judgment under Uncertainty: Heuristics and Biases|date=September 1974|journal=Science|issue=4157|doi=10.1126/science.185.4157.1124|volume=185|pages=1124–31|bibcode=1974Sci...185.1124T|pmid=17835457|vauthors=Tversky A, Kahneman D|s2cid=143452957}}</ref> 其他認知偏差是人類處理能力極限的“副產品”<ref name="Haselton_20052">{{cite book|vauthors=Haselton MG, Nettle D, Andrews PW|chapter=The evolution of cognitive bias.|year=2005|location=Hoboken, NJ, US|publisher=John Wiley & Sons Inc|veditors=Buss DM|title=The Handbook of Evolutionary Psychology|pages=724–746}}</ref>，是由於缺乏適當的心理機制（[[有限理性|有限理性]]）、個人體質和生物狀態的影響（參見[[體化認知|體化認知]]），或僅僅是由於處理資訊能力的極限。<ref>{{cite book|vauthors=Bless H, Fiedler K, Strack F|title=Social cognition: How individuals construct social reality.|url=https://archive.org/details/socialcognitionh0000bles|year=2004|publisher=Hove and New York: Psychology Press.}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Associative processes in intuitive judgment|date=October 2010|journal=Trends in Cognitive Sciences|issue=10|doi=10.1016/j.tics.2010.07.004|volume=14|pages=435–40|pmc=5378157|pmid=20696611|vauthors=Morewedge CK, Kahneman D}}</ref>

在[[認知科學|認知科學]]、[[社會心理學|社會心理學]]和[[行為經濟學|行為經濟學]]的人類判斷和決策研究的過去累積中，已經確定了[[認知偏誤列表|一系列不斷發展的認知偏差]]。 1996年，[[丹尼尔·卡尼曼|丹尼爾·康納曼]]和Tversky發表論文，表示認知偏差對臨床判斷、創業、金融和管理等領域具有有效的實際意義。<ref>{{cite journal|title=On the reality of cognitive illusions|url=http://psy.ucsd.edu/%7Emckenzie/KahnemanTversky1996PsychRev.pdf|date=July 1996|journal=Psychological Review|issue=3|doi=10.1037/0033-295X.103.3.582|volume=103|pages=582–91; discussion 592–6|pmid=8759048|vauthors=Kahneman D, Tversky A|citeseerx=10.1.1.174.5117}}</ref><ref name="S.X. Zhang and J. Cueto 2015">{{cite journal|title=The Study of Bias in Entrepreneurship|url=http://psyarxiv.com/76rkv/|journal=Entrepreneurship Theory and Practice|issue=3|doi=10.1111/etap.12212|year=2015|volume=41|pages=419–454|vauthors=Zhang SX, Cueto J|s2cid=146617323}}</ref>

